            <h2>Skills</h2>
            <p>

                Skills are reusable, packaged capabilities that give Claude Code specialized knowledge and workflows for a specific task. A skill bundles instructions (and optionally scripts and resources) that Claude loads on demand when your request matches what the skill is for.
                You invoke a skill the same way you run any slash command &mdash; by typing <code>/</code> followed by the skill name &mdash; or Claude Code can trigger a relevant skill automatically when it recognizes the task. Examples of what skills can do:
                <ul>
                    <li>Run a structured code review of the current diff.</li>
                    <li>Perform deep, multi-source research and produce a cited report.</li>
                    <li>Design and configure hooks, keybindings, or settings.</li>
                    <li>Build data visualizations that follow a consistent design system.</li>
                </ul>
                Skills keep your prompts short and your results consistent, because the detailed know-how lives in the skill rather than in every message you type. You can use the skills that ship with Claude Code, install skills from plugins, or author your own.

            </p>
